Description: QA Cafe is a provider of test tools for broadband and home network premises equipment (CPE).

CDRouter is used by companies world wide to test a broad range of CPE functionality ranging from NAT, DHCP, PPPoE, and VPNs to evolving protocols such as IPv6 and TR-069. Description: ThermoEnergy is engaged in the worldwide development of municipal and industrial wastewater treatment and power generation technologies.

Our award-winning wastewater recovery systems provide superior process economics and environmental compliance for a variety of industrial and municipal water treatment facilities. The Company's water division, specializing in custom-designed, turn-key solutions for a wide variety of clients, is being managed from its offices in Worcester, Massachusetts corporate headquarters, In addition, the Company has established a broad network of independent dealers and representatives throughout the US. ThermoEnergy’s clean combustion technology, Pressurized Oxy-Combustion ( POXC™), will allow power producers and manufacturers that rely on conventional fossil fuels to take advantage of cheaper energy sources while eliminating virtually all air emissions, as well as achieving full CO2 capture. With POXC™, toxic air emissions from stationary power plants will become a thing of the past. The Company is pursuing the commercialization of POXC™ through the Unity Power Alliance. ThermoEnergy's corporate mission is to continue to grow its market share and technological leadership within the global municipal/industrial wastewater treatment and power generation industries.

Description: We have been investing in tax liens for the past 5 years, starting with a small (friends and family) and growing it conservatively.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: We have been investing in tax liens for the past 5 years, starting with a small (friends and family) and growing it conservatively and quickly into a sizable fund today. We invest in four primary states: Arizona, Georgia, South Carolina, and Maryland. Our primary focus has been on residential properties, both improved and unimproved. We have secured liens on city homes, farms, lakefront cottages,...etc.     The majority of liens in the industry are redeemed by the owner (up to 98%), who pays the county his back-taxes, as well as interest payments to us. Owners who do not redeem and pay what they owe are susceptible to foreclosure, giving us triple digit returns.    Our target return is 100% net which we will share 50/50 with our investors. We enhance our returns by shortening the payment cycle of the lien repayment, and getting these investment funds back to work quicker.     We have developed sophisticated, proprietary software tools that automate every facet of the preliminary research that we do on each lien. Once we have a filtered shortlist of eligible liens, we manually scrutinize them, making sure we are aware of the collateral's criteria. We will also physically visit every lien's property that we are bidding on.    Tax liens are a superior way to make exceptional returns with minimal risk. We treat investor's money like its our own, and will not take any chances with it. Your investment is collateralized twice, once with the actual investment, and second with our funds, invested side by side with yours.    In the last 12 months, our best deals were:  Bought unimproved lot tax lien for $27K, sold 14 months later for $90K  Bought improved vacation home for $80K, sold 2 months later for $110K  Bought improved residential home for $95K, listed 1 year later for $199K  Bought improved residential home for $50K, will list for sale for $150K.

Description: CuraMedix is a medical equipment supplier.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: CuraMedix provides medical radial pressure waves, focused shock waves, and magneto transduction devices. CuraMedix offers healthcare providers shock wave therapy, EMTT, and other regenerative solutions. A variety of evidence-based technologies are available for the treatment of patients with overuse and soft tissue injuries, including extracorporeal pulse activation therapy, extracorporeal shock wave therapy, and extracorporeal magneto transduction therapy.
Industry Groups: Health Care, Manufacturing, Sales and Marketing
